  {
    "id": "98d7d558-510c-479b-af94-377a565f5324",
    "title": "API exposure hardening pass (Copyshop Backend)",
    "details": "Review public API surface, lock down customer history/auth, protect uploads with signed access, and tighten rate limits/logging.\n\n**Security review completed by Grok subagent.**\n\n### Findings Summary\n| Gap | Risk |\n|-----|------|\n| Unauthenticated order creation | Spam/DoS |\n| Public admin dashboard (`/admin`) | Unauthorized UI access |\n| Public static uploads (`/uploads/...`) | File enumeration, no signed URLs |\n| DeviceId-based order leak | Privacy exposure |\n| No request/logging | Audit gaps |\n| Single shared ADMIN_TOKEN | Token leakage = full compromise |\n\n### Remediation (ordered)\n1. Protect `POST /api/orders` with ORDER_API_KEY or device-level auth.\n2. Add `requireAdmin` middleware to `/admin` static route.\n3. Secure `/uploads` with auth or signed URLs (e.g., token-based lookup in DB).\n4. Add auth to `GET /api/orders?deviceId=...` or scope it strictly.\n5. Add request/access logging (e.g., morgan).\n6. Consider JWT/session-based admin auth instead of shared token.\n\n**Action: Present this report to user for prioritization before implementation.**",
    "type": "one-off",
    "status": "in_progress",
    "priority": "critical",
    "dueDate": "2026-02-26",
    "schedule": null,
    "milestones": [
      "Map all externally reachable endpoints",
      "Add auth requirement for customer history endpoints",
      "Protect uploads from direct public enumeration",
      "Apply per-route rate limits and document security model"
    ],
    "automationPrompt": null,
    "lastRunAt": "2026-02-25T22:50:00Z",
    "lastRunStatus": null,
    "cronJobId": null,
    "createdAt": "2026-02-23T15:33:31Z",
    "updatedAt": "2026-02-25T22:50:00Z"
  },
